=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_VarSaw_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 200 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 200.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -5.6602
  harmonic_regularity: 0.6357
  pitch_clarity: 35.8095
  inharmonicity: 0.0052
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -21.6060
  resonance_freq: 301.4648

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: VarSaw Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/VarSaw.html
// Tags: VarSaw, Classes, oscillator
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// observe different duty widths
{ VarSaw.ar(1000, 0, [0, 0.5, 1]) }.plot

(
play({
    VarSaw.ar(
        LFPulse.kr(3, 0, 0.3, 200, 200),
        0,
        LFTri.kr(1.0).range(0, 1), // width
        0.1)
});
)

play({ VarSaw.ar(LFPulse.kr(3, 0, 0.3, 200, 200), 0, 0.2, 0.1) });

// compare:

play({ LFPulse.ar(LFPulse.kr(3, 0, 0.3, 200, 200), 0, 0.2, 0.1) });
